[1] Oregon (Benton County)
Date: Fri 10 Apr 2015
Source: Gazette-Times [edited]
http://www.gazettetimes.com/news/local/new-pertussis-cases-confirmed-at-chs/article_add88742-560a-5854-8b2a-f8fd7c899362.html


Corvallis School District has announced 2 new laboratory-confirmed cases of pertussis at Corvallis High School. Pertussis, commonly known as whooping cough, has broken out at local schools several times this school year [2014-15]. A Benton County Health Department official said there have been close to 40 confirmed cases in the county between October 2014 and March 2015.

Pertussis is a vaccine-preventable illness that is particularly dangerous to infants. It is marked by coughing so vigorous that the afflicted person must struggle for breath, causing a whooping sound. Health officials emphasize that all people coming into contact with infants have a pertussis vaccination to reduce the risk of infecting the child.

