[4] Utah (Summit County)
Date: Wed 8 Apr 2015
Source: Vaccine News Daily Reports [edited]
http://vaccinenewsdaily.com/news/333382-park-city-utah-sees-whooping-cough-outbreak/


As many as 63 cases of pertussis, or whooping cough, in children have been reported recently by Utah's Summit County Health Department. Pertussis, a highly contagious respiratory disease, has a 21-day incubation period.

"We will be seeing cases for a while longer," Summit County Health Department nursing director Carolyn Rose said in a telephone interview with Vaccine News Daily. "We have 62 to 63 cases, but that changes daily." To combat the spread of pertussis in its elementary schools, Park City School District officials and the health department have mandated that children who have not been vaccinated for pertussis stay home from school for 21 days or complete a course of antibiotics.

"A lot of the cases are in that 3- to 5-year range, right before kids get boosters before they go into kindergarten," Rose said.

The CDC says the best way to prevent pertussis is to get vaccinated.

